    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-07-10T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-07-10T18:00:00-05:00" n="189"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d189">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/7–147: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-07-10T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 10, 1947—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>850. Following precedent set in your conversation with Generalissimo re
                    conditions in Formosa,<note n="23" xml:id="d189fn1">See telegram No. 689, March
                        29, 5 p.m., from the Ambassador in China, <ref target="#pg_89">p.
                        89</ref>.</note> suggest you communicate orally to <pb facs="0242" n="232"
                        xml:id="pg_232"/> Generalissimo observations made in Mukden’s 189 June
                        23<note n="24" xml:id="d189fn2">See telegram No. 1435, July 1, 3 p.m., from
                        the Ambassador in China, <ref target="#pg_209">p. 209</ref>.</note>
                    (beginning para 5 “Nationalist southern military” and ending para 8 “into
                    intramural China”). Without associating yourself with views expressed, you may
                    say that info comes to you from responsible confidential observers in
                    Manchuria.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
